    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the established and FDA-recognized regulatory standard for pedicle screw construct testing; no additional test conditions are required to support the regulatory submission. All three QoIs satisfy both the <10% relative difference and E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criteria across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU.",
